<paragraph id="8BA84A2BFFE0AB713CCF4ED8FAA2FD81" blockId="5.[150,1436,394,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Note: 
<emphasis id="B9639639FFE0AB713C834ED8FF5EFE1D" box="[218,244,394,419]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">—</emphasis>
There were five original elements of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1731A8FFE0AB713EE44ED8FC67FE1D" authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1911" box="[701,973,394,419]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Dryopteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kawakamii">
<emphasis id="B9639639FFE0AB713EE44ED8FC67FE1D" box="[701,973,394,419]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Dryopteris kawakamii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available for lectotypification: TAIF- 1004, TAIF-1005, TI-0112, TI-0114 and the photo of TI-0112 published in 
<emphasis id="B9639639FFE0AB71385A4EE3FB10FE74" box="[1027,1210,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Ic. Fl. 
<collectingCountry id="F3000ABBFFE0AB7138094EE3FB10FE74" box="[1104,1210,433,458]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Formosa</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
4: 155. f. 96. 1911. The citation of TAIF-1005 by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8637DAFFE0AB713DA64E8AFD71FE4C" author="Chiou, W. - L. &amp; Yang, K. - C. &amp; Yang, Yuen-Po &amp; Hsu, K. - S. &amp; Chen, S. - Y." box="[511,731,472,498]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refId="ref7351" refString="Chiou, W. - L., Yang, K. - C., Yang, Yuen-Po, Hsu, K. - S. &amp; Chen, S. - Y. (2000) Type specimens in the herbarium of Taiwan Forestry" type="book" year="2000">
Chiou 
<emphasis id="B9639639FFE0AB713E164E8AFD21FE4F" box="[591,651,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2000
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 46) is accepted here as lectotypification although their citation is not indicated by the term “ 
<typeStatus id="54ACF489FFE0AB713E174EACFD65FDA6" box="[590,719,510,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">lectotypus</typeStatus>
”, or its abbreviation, or its equivalent in a modern language. Article 9.21 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8637DAFFE0AB713D6B4D77FDB1FD81" author="McNeill, J. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Burdet, H. M. &amp; Demoulin, V. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; Nicolson, D. H. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Silva, P. C. &amp; Skog, J. E. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J. &amp; Liechtenstein, A. R. G." box="[306,539,549,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refId="ref8180" refString="McNeill, J., Barrie, F. R., Burdet, H. M., Demoulin, V., Hawksworth, D. L., Marhold, K., Nicolson, D. H., Prado, J., Silva, P. C., Skog, J. E., Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J. (eds.) (2006) International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code). Ruggell, Liechtenstein, A. R. G. Gantner Verlag." type="book" year="2006">
McNeill 
<emphasis id="B9639639FFE0AB713DC44D77FE7DFD80" box="[413,471,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
) is not applicable because Chiou 
<emphasis id="B9639639FFE0AB713FFC4D77FC75FD80" box="[933,991,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
’s citation is before 2001.
</paragraph>
